            <entry>
              <b>Create the Sandbox Environment</b>
              <p> Log into the <xref href="https://horizon.hpcloud.com/" scope="external"
                  format="html">Horizon console</xref> using the HPE Helion Public
                <!--A BR tag was used here in the original source.-->Cloud username and password
                that you created <!--A BR tag was used here in the original source.--> during
                  registration.<!--A BR tag was used here in the original source.--><image
                  href="http://docs.hpcloud.com/media/quickstartWest.png" placement="break"
                  id="image_czx_zkp_js"/>
              </p><ol>
                <li>In the <b>US West section</b>, in the <b>Compute</b> row, click <b>Activate</b>
                  <!--A BR tag was used here in the original source.-->to activate the Compute
                  service.<!--A BR tag was used here in the original source.-->Activating the
                  Compute service is required for
                  creating<!--A BR tag was used here in the original source.--> VM
                    instances.<!--A BR tag was used here in the original source.--><image
                    href="http://docs.hpcloud.com/media/quickstartWestActivate.png"
                    placement="break"/>
                </li>
                <li>Click the <b>Project</b> panel and then the <b>Compute</b>
                    sub-panel.<!--A BR tag was used here in the original source.--><image
                    href="http://docs.hpcloud.com/media/quickstartC11.png" placement="break"/>
                </li>
                <li> Download the configuration file (RC file). RC files contain information about a
                  hosted service, including region, tenant, and other information required to create
                  a cluster. This RC file has been pre-configured for this sandbox project.<ol>
                    <li>Click <b>Access &amp; Security</b> and then click the <b>API Access</b>
                      tab.</li>
                    <li> Click <b>Download OpenStack(R) RC file</b>.<image
                        href="http://docs.hpcloud.com/media/quickstartDownloadRCFile_small.png"
                        placement="break"/></li>
                  </ol>
                </li>
                <li>Create a key pair.<ol>
                    <li>Click on the <b>Compute</b> sub-panel and then click <b>Access &amp;
                        Security</b>.</li>
                    <li>Click on the <b>Key Pairs</b> tab and then click <b>+ Create Key
                        Pair</b>.<image href="http://docs.hpcloud.com/media/quickstartE11_small.png"
                        placement="break"/>
                    </li>
                    <li>Enter a name in the <b>Key Pair Name</b> field and then click <b>Create Key
                        Pair</b>.<image
                        href="http://docs.hpcloud.com/media/quickstartkeypair_small.png"
                        placement="break"/>
                    </li>
                    <li>Save the <varname>keyPairName.pem</varname> file somewhere convenient. If
                      you are not automatically prompted to save the file, click the link to
                      download it. This file contains the RSA private key that you will need when
                      you SSH into your VM instance. </li>
                  </ol></li>
              </ol></entry>
